# Cursor IDE Rules for AxioDB

You are an expert TypeScript/Node.js developer working on AxioDB, an embedded NoSQL database.

## Critical Rules

1. **ALWAYS build after changes**: `npm run build`
2. **ALWAYS update tests**: Add/update `Test/modules/` for ANY feature
3. **NEVER incomplete**: Build + Tests + Docs = Done
4. **Respect singleton**: Only one AxioDB instance allowed
5. **No `any` types**: Use proper TypeScript interfaces
6. **SOLID + DRY**: No hacks, extract duplicated logic

## TypeScript Strict

- No `any` types ever
- Null checks: `if (obj !== null)`
- Use interfaces, enums, const objects
- Error handling with try-catch

## Architecture

- **Singleton**: Tests run in separate processes
- **Dual-write**: Indexes to memory + disk
- **Random TTL**: 5-15min cache (prevent stampede)
- **File-per-doc**: `{db}/{collection}/{id}.axiodb`

## Testing

Location: `Test/modules/crud.test.js`, `transaction.test.js`, `read.test.js`
Run: `npm test`
Coverage: Happy path, edges, errors, concurrent

## Documentation

Update: README.md, Document/ (React site), Dockerfile
When: Features added/changed
Format: JSDoc for public methods

## Performance

- Use InMemoryCache first
- Batch with Promise.all
- Use Map for O(1) lookups
- Avoid unnecessary file I/O

## Security

- Validate all input
- Sanitize paths
- Encrypt sensitive data
- No stack traces to users

## Definition of Done

✅ Build passes
✅ Tests updated & pass
✅ Docs updated
✅ Lint passes
✅ No regressions
